<HL>
   Coastal, Arkla Units Set Pact
</HL>
<DATE>
07/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CGP ALG PEG
</CO>
<LP>
   HOUSTON -- The Coastal Gas Marketing Co. unit of Coastal
Corp., an energy holding company, said it signed a 12-year
contract with the Arkla Energy Marketing Co. unit of Arkla
Inc., a natural gas concern, to purchase as much as 7.3
billion cubic feet of natural gas a year. Terms weren't
disclosed.
   Coastal said the gas will be sold to a cogeneration plant
jointly held by it and the Public Service Electric &amp; Gas unit
of Public Service Enterprise Group Inc. of Newark, N.J. The
plant is at Coastal's Eagle Point refinery in New Jersey.
</LP>
