   Sales of New Cars in Europe
</HL>
<DATE>
07/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   LONDON -- Sales of new cars in Europe in May rose 3.8%
from a year earlier and 1.8% from April, but analysts said
the performance doesn't alter their view of underlying
sluggishness or their forecasts for continuing flat sales
this year.
   The April sales were down 4.3% from a year earlier. The
data are from industries and governments in the 12 countries
that normally account for 94% of noncommunist Europe's
passenger car sales.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   A booming West German economy and buoyant French market
headed growth in the latest month, countered by declines in
Britain and Spain, where consumers are subject to tight
monetary regimes.
