   METALCLAD Corp. (Anaheim, Calif.) -- Mark Tomberlin was
named acting chief executive officer of this industrial
insulation contracting company. He succeeds Leland E.
Sweetser, 62 years old, who retains his post as chairman. Mr.
Tomberlin, 38, had served as chief financial officer. Bruce
Haglund, a board member, said Mr. Tomberlin had been named
acting chief executive to give him time to help formulate a
long-term plan for the company and gain some operating
experience. Glenn W. Mayer, 39, was elected president of
Metalclad's principal unit, Metalclad Insulation. He succeeds
Russell Saunders, 70, who is retiring.
