   `Small Loss' in 4th Quarter
</HL>
<DATE>
07/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4
</SO>
<CO>
   HAN SCO
</CO>
<IN>
OFFICE EQUIPMENT (OFF)
</IN>
<LP>
   Smith Corona Corp. said it expects to post a "small loss"
for the fourth quarter ended June 30 and that officials will
recommend a dividend cut.
   G. Lee Thompson, chairman and chief executive officer,
said management will recommend that the quarterly dividend be
reduced to about five cents a share after a scheduled
15-cent-a-share dividend is paid Friday.
</LP>
