   Universal Ogden, with 3,000 employees, will serve roughly
50,000 meals daily; it is expected to have revenue of $135
million for 1991, an Ogden spokesman said.
   Universal Services was founded in 1946 to house and feed
the large work force rebuilding defense bases in Alaska
following World War II. Ogden, in a statement, said a
division of Ogden Allied Services pioneered the remote site
catering business to the oil and and gas drilling industries
in the Gulf of Mexico.
