<HL>
   Business Brief -- Foremost Corp. of America:
   Home Insurance Firm Halts
   5-Month Search for a Buyer
</HL>
<DATE>
07/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   FCOA
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Foremost Corp. of America, Grand Rapids, Mich., said it
had ended a five-month search for a buyer for the company.
   "We have proceeded diligently over the past five months in
identifying and contacting potential purchasers," said
Richard L. Antonini, Foremost's president and chief executive
officer. "Our efforts, however, have been unsuccessful and,
accordingly, the board has determined that it is not in the
best interests of the company and its stockholders to
continue to explore a possible sale."
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Foremost, which provides insurance for manufactured homes
and recreational vehicles, lost $20.8 million in 1989. For
the quarter ended March 31, Foremost posted earnings of $5.2
million, down from $11.9 million a year earlier.
</TEXT>
